Follow-up On April 26, South China Normal University issued a statement, saying that the online claims that "the college threatened students to graduate by hand-copying graduation theses" and "hand-copying graduation theses is tied to teacher certification/teaching evaluation" are untrue. 
At present, the School of Arts will optimize and adjust the practice of students hand-copying graduation theses.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On April 26, on the streets of Shijiazhuang, Hebei, two sanitation workers squatted on the roadside and used an electronic scale to measure the weight of the dust on the ground.
In response, the local sanitation brigade staff told reporters that the city has an assessment of "cleanliness by gram", and if the standard is not met, the frequency of cleaning will be increased, and there will be rewards if the standard is met.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: April 25 (Released) In Leshan, Sichuan, a drunk driver was chased by several people after he hit and ran, but afterwards the local traffic police claimed that the other party did not subjectively hit and run, but just went to the toilet.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
April 26 (Released) Shenzhen, Guangdong.
Employees of Fuyong Weichuan Electronics Factory went on strike to protect their rights. According to the employees who participated in the rights protection, the base salary of level 6 employees is 3,300 yuan, and they are required to work in three shifts. When the project is offline, they force employees to resign, and security guards even beat employees.

April 27, Wuhan, Hubei. Wuhan Excellence City's delivery of buildings was left unfinished.
Owners gathered in front of the sales office and the district government to defend their rights. During the period, they had a physical conflict with the men in black. Some owners were forcibly carried away.
